 different eras, as it evolved from the plaything of European aristocrats to companion of people of all classes and cultures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMusicxSocial aspects. 0aPianoxHistory. 7aMUSIC / Musical Instruments / Piano & Keyboard.2bisacsh1 aBurns, Martha Dennis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChanan, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEyerman, Charlotte N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGood, Edwin M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirai, Atsuko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoover, Cynthia Adams, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeppert, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParakilas, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaykoff, Ivan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTick, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTsvetaeva, Marina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTucker, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWheelock, Gretchen A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZank, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013082940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300130829423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300130829/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a